        "title": "How to enforce the concrete class take a concrete instance as argument?",
        "body": "<p>Here is my use case,<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public interface dataModel {\n   //nothing\n}\npublic interface dataRepo {\n    public doIt(dataModel a);\n}\npublic class concreteDataModel implements dataModel {\n    public doIt(dataModel a);\n}\npublic class concreteDataRepo implements dataRepo {\n    public doIt(dataModel a);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I feel like i am doing this wrong.  I have several datarepo and datamodel. I want the repo takes the datamodel of its own kind. Is there any design pattern to make this clean?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 29734696,
